<section id="itsm_locQualityIssueSeverity">
    <title>its_locQualityIssueSeverity</title>
    
    <para>Localization Quality Issue Severity - the <code>its_locQualityIssueSeverity</code>
        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>property<?oxy_custom_end?>
        is the <olink targetdoc="../xliff21.xml" targetptr="ITS20">[ITS]</olink> defined
            <code>its_locQualityIssueSeverity</code>
        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>property<?oxy_custom_end?>. </para>
    <para>This
        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>property<?oxy_custom_end?>
        provides the severity score for a particular issue, the higher the number the higher the
        severity. Tools are expected to interpret this score within their own severity rating
        system.</para>
    <para><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="140,255,140"?><emphasis>Contains:</emphasis>
        number.<?oxy_custom_end?></para>
    
    <para><emphasis>Value description:</emphasis> a floating point number between 0.0 and 100.0,
        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="140,255,140"?>inclusive<?oxy_custom_end?>.</para>
        
    <para><emphasis>Default value:</emphasis>
        undefined<?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>.<?oxy_custom_end?></para>
    
    <warning><para>The <link linkend="itsm_locQualityIssueSeverity">its_locQualityIssueSeverity</link>
            <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>property<?oxy_custom_end?>
            is intended to be used in concert with the <olink
                targetdoc="itsm_locQualityIssueProfileRef.xml"
                targetptr="itsm_locQualityIssueProfileRef"
                    ><code>its_locQualityIssueProfileRef</code></olink>
            <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>property<?oxy_custom_end?>
            that is to provide information on the applicable Quality Model. Without providng quality
            model information, the severity score between 0 and 100 is very likely to be useless and
            not interoperable.</para> </warning>
    
    
    <para><emphasis>Used in:</emphasis>
        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,64,0"?><olink
            targetdoc="../../elements/inline/mrk.xml" targetptr="mrk"><code>&lt;mrk></code></olink>
        and <?oxy_custom_end?><olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/sm.xml" targetptr="sm"
                ><code>sm</code></olink>, or in <olink
            targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_locQualityIssue.xml"
            targetptr="itsm_locQualityIssue"><code>its_locQualityIssues</code></olink>
        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>array
        elements<?oxy_custom_end?>.</para>
    
    
    <para>See the <olink targetdoc="../../modules/itsm/Localization_Quality_Issue.xml"
            targetptr="lqiAnnotation">ITS Localization Quality Issue Annotation</olink> for the
        normative usage description of this
        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>property<?oxy_custom_end?>
        when used inline; advanced Constraints follow from that normative usage description.</para>
    <para>See <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_locQualityIssue.xml"
            targetptr="itsm_locQualityIssue"><code>its_locQualityIssues</code></olink> for standoff
        usage Constraints.</para>
</section>
